goit-py_web-hw-06
🔧 Project Description
This project provides a PostgreSQL database deployed using Docker, along with Python scripts for working with the database, including executing SQL queries.

🔁 Installation and Setup
1. 🔒 Requirements
Docker installed on your machine.
Docker Compose for container management.
2. 🛠️ Installation
Clone the repository:
bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/goit-py_web-hw-06.git
cd goit-py_web-hw-06
Create and configure the containers:
bash
docker-compose up -d
This will create and start a PostgreSQL container. SQL scripts located in the db/ folder will be executed automatically.
3. 🗒 Executing Queries
Place SQL queries in the sql_request/ folder.
Use the Python script to execute the queries.
Example of executing a query from a file:
bash
poetry run python py_request/query_1.py

🛠️ Technologies Used
Python
PostgreSQL
Docker / Docker Compose
